title: Gisaengchung
overview: Greed and class discrimination threaten the newly formed symbiotic relationship between the wealthy Park family and the destitute Kim clan.

title: Barton Fink
overview: A renowned New York playwright is enticed to California to write for the movies and discovers the hellish truth of Hollywood.

title: Perfetti sconosciuti
overview: Seven long-time friends get together for a dinner. When they decide to share with each other the content of every text message, email and phone call they receive, many secrets start to unveil and the equilibrium trembles.

title: Druk
overview: Four friends, all high school teachers, test a theory that they will improve their lives by maintaining a constant level of alcohol in their blood.

title: La dolce vita
overview: A series of stories following a week in the life of a philandering paparazzo journalist living in Rome.

title: Happiness
overview: The lives of several individuals intertwine as they go about their lives in their own unique ways, engaging in acts society as a whole might find disturbing in a desperate search for human connection.

title: The Station Agent
overview: When his only friend dies, a man born with dwarfism moves to rural New Jersey to live a life of solitude, only to meet a chatty hot dog vendor and a woman dealing with her own personal loss.

title: The Royal Tenenbaums
overview: The eccentric members of a dysfunctional family reluctantly gather under the same roof for various reasons.

title: Heat
overview: A group of professional bank robbers start to feel the heat from police when they unknowingly leave a clue at their latest heist.

title: Crash
overview: Los Angeles citizens with vastly separate lives collide in interweaving stories of race, loss and redemption.

title: Underground
overview: A group of Serbian socialists prepares for the war in a surreal underground filled by parties, tragedies, love and hate.

title: Nueve reinas
overview: Two con artists try to swindle a stamp collector by selling him a sheet of counterfeit rare stamps (the "nine queens").

title: Modern Times
overview: The Tramp struggles to live in modern industrial society with the help of a young homeless woman.

title: Secrets & Lies
overview: Following the death of her adoptive parents, a successful young black optometrist establishes contact with her biological mother -- a lonely white factory worker living in poverty in East London.

title: Chhichhore
overview: A tragic incident forces Anirudh, a middle-aged man, to take a trip down memory lane and reminisce his college days along with his friends, who were labelled as losers.

title: Naked
overview: Parallel tales of two sexually obsessed men, one hurting and annoying women physically and mentally, one wandering around the city talking to strangers and experiencing dimensions of life.

title: Yeopgijeogin geunyeo
overview: A young man sees a drunk, cute woman standing too close to the tracks at a metro station in Seoul and pulls her back. She ends up getting him into trouble repeatedly after that, starting on the train.

title: Vizontele
overview: Lives of residents in a small Anatolian village change when television is introduced to them

title: Special Chabbis
overview: A gang of con-men rob prominent rich businessmen and politicians by posing as C.B.I and income tax officers.

title: 3 Idiots
overview: Two friends are searching for their long lost companion. They revisit their college days and recall the memories of their friend who inspired them to think differently, even as the rest of the world called them "idiots".
